</span>.</dd></dl>

<p id="mwAWU">Passive radar is applicable to <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Electronic_countermeasures" title="Electronic countermeasures" id="mwAWY" class="mw-redirect">electronic countermeasures</a> and <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Radio_astronomy" title="Radio astronomy" id="mwAWc">radio astronomy</a> as follows:</p>

<dl id="mwAWg"><dd id="mwAWk"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt349" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"F_D = F_T \\times \\left (\\frac {V_R}{C} \\right)"}}' id="mwAWo"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle F_{D}=F_{T}\times \left({\frac {V_{R}}{C}}\right)}">
  <semantics>
